dct_title_s: The Province of New Jersey, divided into east and west, commonly called the Jerseys
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by shading. Shows county boundaries and "Division line run in 1743 between East New Jersey and West New Jersey." "This map has been drawn from the survey ... by Bernard Ratzer ... and from another large survey ... by Gerard Banker." "Fac-simile of map now in possession of Chas. D. Deshler ... of New Brunswick."
dct_publisher_sm: [Trenton] : Geological Survey of New Jersey, 1877 (N. Y. : Photo. lith. by J. Bien).
